{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ideec2e7da-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1511"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1511"},"text":"§ 1511.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Tax exemption","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Corporation, including its franchise, its capital, reserves, and surplus, and its income and property, shall be exempt from all taxation on or after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-02-16"},"text":"February 16, 1938","children":[],"tail":", imposed by the United States or by any Territory, dependency, or possession thereof, or by any State, county, municipality, or local taxing authority. A contract of insurance of the Corporation, and a contract of insurance reinsured by the Corporation, shall be exempt from taxation imposed by any State, municipality, or local taxing authority."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ideec2e7db-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-02-16/ch30"},"text":"Feb. 16, 1938, ch. 30","children":[],"tail":", title V, § 511, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/75"},"text":"52 Stat. 75","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/354/tI/s108"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–354, title I, § 108","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3197"},"text":"108 Stat. 3197","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ideec2e7dc-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ideec2e7dd-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","